1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 Tomato
1 Cucumber
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Halloumi
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 tbs honey
1 drizzle olive oil
1 drizzle white wine vinegar

• Slice cucumber into thin sticks. Thinly slice tomato into wedges.
• Cut halloumi into 1cm-thick slices.
• In a small bowl, combine lemon pepper spice blend, the honey and a splash of water.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook halloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add lemon pepper mixture and turn to coat.

• Meanwhile, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Season and set aside.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Build your tacos by topping tortillas with salad, lemon pepper halloumi and cucumber.
• Drizzle over Greek-style yoghurt to serve. Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese. Enjoy!